<span class="header1">BUSINESS & COMMUNITY SERVICE</span>
<p>If you worked within this occupational field, a community or business would hire you. These occupations are physically demanding. To enjoy them, you must like adventure.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Sheriff</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A sheriff is very much like a police officer. Usually a sheriff works for a small town, community, or county that cannot afford a police force. If you were a sheriff, you would keep the community safe. You might direct traffic, settle arguments, and investigate crimes. Also, you would schedule and oversee any deputy sheriffs who worked for the same community.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a high school diploma for this job.  Many communities or towns want someone with a college education or years of experience in law enforcement. Most sheriffs must pass a written exam. They must also meet some physical requirements.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary of a sheriff depends on how much money the community can afford to pay. Some communities pay as little as $25,000.  Others may pay as much as $65,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Deputy Sheriff</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a deputy sheriff, you would help the sheriff enforce the laws of a small town that has no police department. Your duties might include directing traffic, writing tickets, settling arguments, and investigating crimes. You would perform many of the same duties as the sheriff, but you would not manage other employees.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a high school diploma for this job.  Many communities or towns want someone with a college education or years of experience in law enforcement. Most deputy sheriffs must pass a written exam. They must also meet some physical requirements.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary of a deputy sheriff depends on how much money the community can afford to pay. Some communities pay as little as $25,000. Others may pay as much as $65,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Corrections Officer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CF/so000174.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Corrections Officer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A corrections officer works in a jail or prison. As a corrections officer, you would make sure that prisoners were safe. You would also see that they followed the rules of the prison and did not escape. You would search cells for items that the prisoners should not have and report any arguments or fights.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Most law enforcement officers need a high school diploma or pass an equivalency test. Some counties or states prefer those who have taken college courses. Corrections officers cannot have a criminal record. They must have a driver's license, and must be at least 18 years old.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary range is $22,000 to $55,000.</blockquote>

