<span class="header1">BUSINESS & ENVIRONMENT</span>
<p>The occupations in this field protect, manage, or research the environment. If the environment is one of your interests, you might want to consider the occupations in this field. Here are three examples.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Solid Waste Manager</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you want to protect the environment, you might become a solid waste manager. In this job, you would look for the best ways to collect, move, store, and dispose of solid waste. For example, you might make sure that styrofoam cups and other household trash were discarded in a place that would cause as little harm as possible to the environment.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree in a technical field for this job.  Your degree might be in engineering, geology, chemistry, or a related area.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary is from $21,000 to $45,000+.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Park Ranger</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CF/C585042.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Park Ranger" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A park ranger makes sure that visitors and wildlife are safe in state and national parks. As a park ranger, you would patrol the park.  You would also collect fees, provide information about the park, and enforce park rules and regulations.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least 2 years of college courses in science and law enforcement to become a park ranger.  Many of the jobs with the U.S. Forest Service require a ranger to have a Bachelor's Degree.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary you receive as a park ranger is based on your education and experience.  It can range from $30,000 to $73,000+.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Forestry Technician</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CF/43168.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Forestry Technician" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you want to work outdoors, you might become a forestry technician. In this job, you would help a forester oversee logging and tree planting.  You would also help him or her with water regulation and wildlife management. In addition, you might collect information for people who want to know how to protect the forest.  You might also oversee work crews and survey the forest for road construction.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least an Associate's Degree for this job.  Some states require that you take a test and become registered.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The average yearly salary runs from $15,000 to $30,000.</blockquote>

