<span class="header1">BUSINESS & TECHNOLOGY</span>
<p>Technology is becoming more and more important in running an office.  The occupations in this field need people who know how business machines and equipment work. If you enjoy working with equipment or machines, this field may be for you.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Information Manager</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CF/43334.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Information Manager" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>You may have heard the saying that we live in an "Information Age." This means that getting information from one place to another is very important. An information manager makes sure that people within a company can do this. People who work in the same location must be able to communicate with each other.  They must also be able to communicate with people in company offices in different cities.  To do this job well, you must know as much as possible about telephones and computers.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You would need at least a Bachelor's Degree for this job.  Many employers require a Master's Degree.  To teach others in information management, you must have a Ph.D.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $20,000 to $40,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Computer Engineer</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Businesses are always looking for a new way to make their offices run smoother. A computer engineer helps businesses do this. As a computer engineer, you would look for ways to make a business' day-to-day tasks easier. You would make suggestions on which computer systems would be best for the company. You would also help the company come up with new ways to route information. To be a good computer engineer, you must a lot about computers and be able to work with different types of people.  People who do this job are also called computer systems analysts.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma for this job. It is also helpful to have taken courses in computer science, technology and programming.  Experience with computers will help you to get a job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $40,000 to $95,000+.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Computer Service Technician</span><br /><br />
	<!-- <img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CF/1234.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Computer Service Technician" /> -->
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Computers are very important to our society and will continue to be in the future. If you like knowing what makes computers work and want to keep them running, you might become a computer service technician. In this job, you figure out why a computer isn't working and fix it.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma and courses in electronics for this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $40,000 to $68,000.</blockquote>

